dismissalComment.html: Yuvraj falling to spin, not for the last time, pushing forward inside the line, and off stump is knocked back as Tredwell straightens it from round the stumps

commentPreTextItems.html: Chants of 'Dhoni, Dhoni' around the ground

commentTextItems.html: short, and the India captain ends it at his home ground with a powerful pull to the deep square leg boundary

commentPostTextItems.html: Over to the north for the last two games, in Mohali and Dharamsala. Abhishek Purohit signing off. Cheers

Virat Kohli is the Man of the Match. Kohli: "I was batting well for a while, getting out in different ways, got a few good balls, made a few mistakes. Today I just reacted to the way the ball was thrown at me. I did not have to pre-plan which I was doing in the previous games. I was relying on my reflexes. It was a difficult wicket, Finn gets the ball to seam on any wicket. Crowd support was brilliant."

Dhoni: "Bowlers did the job for us. It was important to take wickets with the new ball. 150-odd was not enough to defend for the English side. Gautam batted well with Virat, that was important as the ball was doing something. Most of the bowlers are new. Bhuvi and Shami have just got into the side. They will get a lot of confidence out of this. [When asked if he was nervous as he walked out to bat] Not really, I have played a lot of cricket here. Yuvi got out, so I got an opportunity to bat, at one stage it did not look if I would get to bat. I cannot say it was good that I got to bat, they will beat me in the dressing room. It is one of the best facilities. Execution is very important. Response from the people has been amazing. Everything went off well, we won the game, it was a perfect script."

Cook: "150 was nowhere near enough on that wicket. Credit to India. Not really going to defend that, unless it is a freak day. We did not get out to attacking shots, got out to defensive shots. It is frustrating, We have the potential, but we are not clicking at the moment. The ball skid on slightly better in the second innings, we knew that would happen."
Alan Gardner's match report is already updated here.

So Dhoni has the satisfaction of hitting the winning runs in Ranchi's debut international game. More satisfying for the side will be Virat Kohli's return to his habit of winning chases for India. India's bowlers, a much-maligned lot, will be pleased to have done most of the groundwork for victory. Where do England go from here? Up north to Mohali, with a series to be saved there, and having now lost 18 of their previous 21 ODIs in India.
Sridhar: "Any one willing to treat me!!! My prediction of Dhoni scoring the winning runs came true"

While we wait for the presentation, here's something for you to check out. Ian Chappell, Sachin Tendulkar, Michael Holding, Wasim Akram, Martin Crowe and Mark Taylor - they're all in Talking Cricket, our new hardback anthology of the best interviews from ESPNcricinfo over the years. Now available for online order for customers in India.

dismissalComment.html: Bhuvneshwar striking now, Bell trying to cut one that moved in from a length, clear outside edge and Dhoni has a sharp take standing up

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c Yuvraj Singh b Ashwin 10 (30b 1x4 0x6 39m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: Morgan's fallen to the reverse sweep, he's spooned it in the air from around leg stump to backward point, what a waste of an important wicket, which it always is when all these cute shots don't come off

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Kieswetter b Jadeja 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: this won't do Kieswetter's case any good, lunging forward, leaving a gap between bat and pad, and Jadeja;s flighted arm ball has sneaked in, excellent delivery but Kieswetter not helping himself by bringing the bat down from that angle

headshotImage.caption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Samit Patel lbw b Jadeja 0 (4b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: that looked plumb, Jadeja and his arm ball on fire, tossed up, drawing the batsman forward, Patel playing for the straightening, the ball carries in to hit him in front of off

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root c †Dhoni b Sharma 39 (57b 4x4 0x6 92m) SR: 68.42

dismissalComment.html: got him now, the wide delivery working for Ishant third time, fuller this time, and Root was drawn forward at it, played away from the body with an open face, hint of away movement, and and a tumbling Dhoni snaps up the outside edge, steadying stand broken

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Bresnan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tim Bresnan b Ashwin 25 (37b 3x4 0x6 45m) SR: 67.56

dismissalComment.html: classic from Ashwin, what a refreshing delivery coming from him, tossed up outside off, inviting the drive, Bresnan feeling for it away from the body, and it spins in to bowl him through the gate, Graeme Swann would have been proud, so would have been Prasanna

dismissalText.commentary: Steven Finn c Yuvraj Singh b Raina 3 (12b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: Finn has picked out deep midwicket with the slog sweep and Dhoni is clapping with the big gloves, one of those days for him where everything has worked, after all the defending, England's attempt to get some runs ends in a wicket

dismissalText.commentary: Jade Dernbach b Jadeja 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Jadeja ending the innings with another arm ball, all three of his wickets have come with it, pushed through on a good length, angled in, and enough of a gate on Dernbach's forward push to hit the stumps

dismissalComment.html: Gambhir gives it away against spin, charges out and heaves it wide of mid on, who takes a few steps to his left, and takes a head-high catch quite safely

dismissalText.commentary: Ajinkya Rahane b Finn 0 (4b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Kochi all over again for Rahane and Finn, who rips in a good length delivery through the young batsman's gate, Rahane seemed to have got slightly forward this time, but still left too much between bat and pad, off stump is uprooted
